(154, 'The East Asiatic (Thailand) Public Company Limited  Brenntag', NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '02 689 5999', '', '02 689 5888', '33rd Floor, Lumpini Tower 1168/98-100 and 106 Rama IV Road Thungmahamek, Sathorn Bangkok 10120', '', '', 'The East Asiatic Company Ltd. (The EAC Group) has origins back to 1884, when the Danish sea captain, H N Andersen, established a trading company in Bangkok at Oriental Avenue. This formed the basis for the Group\'s establishment in Denmark in 1897 and listing on the Copenhagen Stock Exchange.\r\n\r\n\r\nThe EAC Group has been undergoing significant restructuring to position ourselves for the challenges of the 21st Century. In the process, EAC has transformed itself into a highly focused enterprise with a solid platform for profitable growth. Today, the Group consists of market leading, consistently profitable consumer, industrial, and service businesses.\r\n\r\nAlthough the EAC Group continues to be a Danish company, listed on the Copenhagen Stock Exchange, its Management is located in Singapore and the geographic focus is on Asia-the origin and historic strength of the company.\r\n\r\nThe EAC Group is intent on creating value for all stakeholders, be they shareholders, customers, suppliers or employees.\r\n\r\n\r\nThe driving force behind the EAC Group has always been the pursuit of excellence and the fundamental objective to conduct long-term profitable business in a responsible manner.\r\n\r\nWhilst the Group has become more focused and targeted, it has never compromised its basic values and its reputation for integrity and fair dealings. This has remained key to the conduct of the Group. Mutuality and reciprocity remain the foundation of our Corporate Culture.\r\n...\r\n&lt;p&gt;Philip Visit and give Brochure + Property Perfect Brochure 14/5/07 Not interesting They. Expat have there own House&lt;/p&gt;', '52', '41', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, '2016-05-17 13:39:20', '177', '23', '2014-01-15', 'http://www.eac.co.th/  www.brenntag-asi