(176, 'Rovi Thai Company DSM Solution Products', NULL, NULL, NULL, '***not specify****', '02-264-9800', '', '02 264 9844 or 264 9899', '17/1 Fl., Maleenont Tower, \n3199 Rama IV Road, Klongton, Klongtoey Bangkok 10110', '', '', '&lt;p&gt;Call 15/2/07 Philip Visit and give Brochure 8/2/07 Expat buy there house and no new come&lt;/p&gt;', '24', '0', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, '2013-10-31 12:06:06', '77', '16', '0000-00-00', 'http://www.dsm.com', '0', '2', '0', 2, '', NULL, '0', '', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL),
(180, 'Ford Motor Company', 231, NULL, NULL, '-', '02-686-4000', '', '02-686-4656', '98 Sathorn Square Office Tower, 12th Floor\r\nNorth Sathorn Road, \r\nSilom, Bang rak\r\nBangkok, 10500', '', '', 'Profile\r\nToday Ford is a major force in the Thai automotive industry, and intends to further expand production to grow its business and achieve maximum customer satisfaction. Ford has invested over $2.35 billion in Thailand since 1995.\r\n\r\nFord in Thailand\r\n\r\nFord operations in Thailand, established in 1996, are responsible for all Ford marketing activities and retail operations in Thailand, controlling nationwide sales distribution of Ford brand products. Ford in Thailand is also a Regional Operating Headquarters (ROH) under the Board of Investment\'s (BOI) promotion, having a function of supporting the ASEAN regional operations. The team provides management, coordination, consultancy and support services for all of its Thailand affiliate and regional operations\r\n\r\nFord Motor Company Thailand \r\n\r\nEstablished in July 2010, Ford Motor Company Thailand is a new, state-of-the-art passenger vehicle manufacturing plant in Rayong, scheduled for completion in 2012. With an initial annual production capacity of 150,000 units, it will be capable of producing a diversified range of Ford\'s global products for Thailand and export markets across the Asia Pacific region. Ford plans to purchase up to US$800 million (THB 26 billion) worth of local components annually through Thailand\'s local supplier network. The new facility has the potential to support up to 11,000 new jobs &ndash; including up to 2,200 direct jobs with Ford, and 8,800 indirect jobs through its supplier and dealer networks. \r\n\r\nAuto Alliance Thailand (AAT) Joint-Venture\r\n\r\nFord returned to Thailand in November 1995 with the formation of AutoAlliance (Thailand) Co., Ltd., a Ford/Mazda joint-venture. This world-class facility, located in Rayong province, represents over $1.5 billion of investment and produces three major models - Ford Fiesta, Ford Ranger and Ford Everest sports utility vehicle. Annual production capacity is 275,000 units and export destinations include over 130 countries across Europe, Asia, Middle East, Australia and Africa. The assembly operations engage with around 165 local parts suppliers.\r\n\r\nHistory of Ford in Thailand\r\n\r\nFord\'s history in Thailand goes as far back as 1913 when the first Ford Model T was sold in the Kingdom. In 1960, Ford was the first company to invest in an assembly operation in Thailand. At that time, the Thai Motor Industry Company was formed as a joint venture between Anglo-Thai Motors and Ford U.K. The assembly operations produced the popular Ford Anglia throughout the 1960s. In 1973, the joint venture was incorporated as a wholly owned subsidiary and renamed Ford Thailand. However, the company decided to cease operations in 1976. \r\n\r\nthey are using Asian Tiger. ', '55', '4', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, '2013-10-31 11:50:08', '77', '24', '2014-01-15', 'www.ford.com', '0', '0', '0', 10, '', NULL, '2', '', '', 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 2, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL),
