(252, 'Lear Corporation Southeast Asia Co Ltd', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'tleaungrungwason@lear.com', '+66 (0) 3762-9870', '', '+66 (0) 3762-9873-4', '246 Times Square Bldg, 26th Fl, Sukhumvit 12-14 Rd, Kwaeng Klongtoey, Khet Klongtoey, Bangkok. 10110', '21557 Telegraph Road\r\nSouthfield, MI 48033\r\n248.447.1500', '612/10 Moo 9. Kabinburi Industrial Zone, Nongki, Kabinburi, \r\nPrachinburi, 25110	', 'Profile\r\nLear was founded in Detroit in 1917 as American Metal Products, a manufacturer of seating assemblies and other components for the automotive and aircraft industries. Lear has grown to meet the changing needs of the industry with 18 major acquisitions since 1994, when Lear went public. \r\n\r\nToday, the Company provides complete automotive seating and electrical power management systems around the globe, including high-power and hybrid electrical components and systems. At Lear, the world-class products are designed, engineered and manufactured by a diverse team of 92,500 employees in 35 countries. Lear is headquartered in Southfield, Michigan and Lear stock is traded on the New York Stock Exchange under the symbol [LEA]. \r\n\r\nThe success is a result of our dedication to providing the best possible products and services to the world&rsquo;s automakers by working in partnership with them to deliver market-leading innovation, value and quality to automotive consumers.\r\n \r\n&lt;p&gt;Philip Visit and give Brochure 9/3/07&lt;/p&gt;', '55', '30', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, '2017-11-08 09:05:26', '128', '24', '2014-01-15', 'www.lear.com', '0', '1', '0', 10, '', NULL, '0', '', '', 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL),
