(877, 'MVM Surveys Thailand Co Ltd', 0, NULL, NULL, 'd_p_kmbl@mvmsurveys.com', '02-617-7660', '', '02-317-7662', '299/46 Areeya Mandarina Village, Sutthisan Winichi Road, Samsennok, Huay Khwang, Bangkok 10320, Thailand\r\n\r\n', '', 'Tel. 66 2274 8711 Fax: 66 22748712\r\n\r\nEmail: \r\n\r\n \r\n ', 'MVM Surveys (Thailand) Co. Ltd. was founded and registered in Thailand in 1999 and is based in Bangkok with a satellite office in Songkhla. MVM has a long history of providing management, quality assurance and quality control, and other expertise in areas of hydrographic surveys, rig positioning, marine engineering surveys and other marine geoscience projects.\r\n\r\nIn 2008 MVM acquired a survey vessel and the appropriate equipment to provide it\'s clients with a cost effective and professional product locally available in Thailand. The MVM team provides an excellent product with respect to the collection, processing, and interpretation of marine geoscience and hydrographic data and produces concise and professional reports on the findings.\r\n\r\nMVM has an established and growing reputation for providing excellent service to our Clients while maintaining a high standard of safety, quality and environmental preservation.\r\n\r\nThailand is MVM\'s primary area of operation, however MVM have successfully completed projects in other SE Asian countries.\r\n\r\nUpdate 8/11/06', '14', '14', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, '2013-11-18 15:51:39', '77', '24', '2014-01-15', 'http://mvmsurveys.com/', '0', '0', '0', 0, '', NULL, '0', '', '', 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL),
(878, 'International Power Plc', 21, NULL, NULL, '', '02 684 6022, 08 4555 7180', '', '02 684 6099', '29th Floor, Q House Lumpini \n1 South Sathorn Road, \nThung Mahamek Sathorn \nBangkok 10120', 'International Power Ltd.\r\nSenator House\r\n85 Queen Victoria Street\r\nLondon EC4V 4DP', '', 'International Power is one of the world\'s leading independent power producers with interests in six core regions globally, owning one of the most geographically diverse portfolios of power plants. We have a strong growth agenda which ensures a host of potential opportunities for employee&rsquo;s intent on making their mark in a growing global organisation.\r\nWe have a large multinational work force in a variety of different roles including engineers, finance managers, business developers and project finance specialists. The company operates in a number of different locations worldwide: we have a head office in London; six regional offices and a variety of asset locations globally.\r\nKey to International Power\'s success is its organisational agility - we therefore place a high priority on the recruitment, retention and training of staff at all levels, whether employed by us directly or by any of our subsidiaries or associates.\r\nWe promote professional and personal development, and actively support formal training programme participation, attendance at internal and external seminars, achievement of professional qualifications, on the job coaching and personal development planning. We encourage our staff to participate actively in their own personal development and in relevant professional organisations.\r\nFind out more about International Power...\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;July 22, 2010. Lyn visited Office. Give The New Bangkok Guide Book for HR copy. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;K. Samaiporn Receptionist &lt;br /&gt;receptionist@gdfsuezmeaa.com &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;K. Patcharee Kampraengkeo (Pok) - resigned already. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;HR &amp;amp; Admin Manager Patcharee.&lt;br /