(887, 'TSL amp Associate Thailand Co Ltd', 0, NULL, NULL, 'padung-99@hotmail.com', '02-251-8130 ,02-263-2527 ,084-439-3317', '', '02-251-8135', '130-132 Sindhorn Building 2nd Floor Tower 1, Patumwan, Bangkok 10330', '', '', 'Over ten years, our firm has successfully handled thousands of immigration cases on behalf of our clients. Cases include non-resident visas: tourist, business, student, work and retirement; and permanent resident visas: employer petitioned and family related - marriage, fianc&eacute;, parents and dependents.\r\n \r\nWe take pride in our work and proven track record of getting results. Every client receives individual attention. We make it a point to know our clients personally, understand their situations, and provide expert information and advice. If circumstances present weak prospects for obtaining a visa, we tell clients honestly and then counsel them on the best alternatives. If there is something our firm can do, we zealously represent our clients utilizing both our knowledge of the law and practical experience&mdash;both of which are necessary components of effective advocacy.\r\n \r\nOur English and Thai speaking counselors conduct initial interviews free of charge. We listen, evaluate each case and explain options clearly and in detail. If retained to assist, we offer most clients a low flat fee. With a decade of experience and careful attention to details, we have learned the most efficient ways to assist and represent clients at each embassy, saving them time and aggravation.\r\n \r\nTo provide additional savings, we do not charge a processing fee for children accompanying their parents on various types of visas -- many firms charge over $200 per child for this service. We also do not charge to have most documents translated.\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;Call and Send E-mail 16/1/07 K. Cherry www.TSLvisaworld.com&lt;/p&gt;', '14', '1', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, '2013-11-19 10:11:14', '77', '1', '2014-01-15', 'http://www.tslthailand.com/index.ph