(1019, 'Linde Thailand PLC formerly Thai Industrial Gases PLC', 217, NULL, NULL, 'siriporn.boonto@tig.boc.com', ' +66.2.3386-338', '', '02 312 0126', '15th Floor, Bangna Tower A, \n2/3 Moo 14, Bangna-Trad Road, (K.M. 6.5) \nT.Bangkaew, Bangplee, \nSamutprakarn 10540', '', '', 'Bangkok, 22 June 2012:  Thai Industrial Gases Public Company Limited (TIG), a member of The Linde Group, today announced its official rebrand as Linde (Thailand) Public Company Limited [&lsquo;Linde Thailand&rsquo;]. The brand change from TIG to Linde is part of a global programme to position the companies within The Linde Group under a single Linde brand.\r\n\r\nLinde is Thailand&rsquo;s leading gases company, with the most comprehensive industrial, specialty and medical gases product portfolio and largest direct sales network across the nation. With more than 40 years of successful operations, the company combines deep local knowledge with global expertise, resources and best operating practices to provide high quality total gas solutions to a variety of industries across Thailand.\r\n\r\nMr Keerin Chutumstid, Managing Director of Linde Thailand said, &ldquo;Today  we celebrate a momentous milestone in our company&rsquo;s history. We are proud to become Linde in Thailand, and aspire to significantly expand our business in the future. With the strong backing of our parent company The Linde Group, we will actively continue to introduce innovative and technology-led solutions that will add value to our customers&rsquo; businesses, and in turn contribute to further economic progress in the country.&rdquo;\r\n\r\nMr Bernd Eulitz, Regional Business Unit Head for Linde&rsquo;s gases business in South &amp; East Asia said, &quot;The Linde Group is very positive about the many opportunities we see in Thailand. We will continue to invest in this important market to further extend our supply and distribution capabilities, and ensure we are well positioned to support our customers in their growth and investment plans here.&rdquo;\r\n\r\nLast July, the company announced that it will invest Bt 3.5 billion to install a new air separation plant in the Eastern Industrial Estate (EIE) at Map Ta Phut, Rayong. This new plant will be the largest liquid air separation plant in the country, capable of producing 800 tons per day of liquefied gases, once it is commissioned in September 2013. Linde Thailand has also invested Bt 417 million to upgrade its infrastructure, including the installation of a new nitrogen compressor and pipeline network at Map Ta Phut.\r\n\r\nFrom 22 June 2012 onwards, the company&rsquo;s new logo will make its appearance on all its corporate signages, communications materials and assets. The conversion period is expected to last several months. \r\n\r\n &lt;p&gt;(TIG) Member of the Linde Group Philip Visit and give Brochure 10/10/07 old client Mrs. Lhmann&lt;/p&gt;', '53', '7', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, '2013-11-23 10:52:59', '77', '24', '2014-01-15', 'http://www.linde.co.th/', '0', '0', '0', 0, '', NULL, '0', '', '', 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL),
(1020, 'SYNTEC Construction Public Co., Ltd.', 0, NULL, NULL, '*', '02 381 6333', '', '02 711 5167', '555/7-11 Soi Sukhumvit 63 (Ekamai)\nSukhumvit Road Klongton Nua \nWattana Bangkok 10110', '', '', 'Syntec Construction Public Company Limited is a construction contractor and engineering company located at 555/7-11 Sukhumvit Soi 63 (Ekamai) Sukhumvit Road, Kwaeng Khlongton Nua, Khet Wattana, Bangkok 10110, telephone no. (662) 023816333, fax no. (662) 02-7115183.\r\n\r\nThe Company started at the end of 1988 as a joint-venture company between one of Thailand\'s leading steel pipe manufacturers and three of Singapore\'s major construction contractors. Blending the strong business connections of the Thai partner with the Singapore partners\' regional experience and expertise in construction and civil engineering, Syntec rose to rank as one of the largest fully integrated construction groups in Thailand. Syntec changed its status to that of a public company in October 1992 and became the youngest Thai construction company to be listed on the Stock Exchange of Thailand in July 1993.\r\n\r\nThe Syntec Group has been grown into a conglomerate of over 30 subsidiaries and associated companies engaged primarily in construction and related activities as well as property development and investment in Thailand and the South-East Asian countries of Malaysia, Singapore, Myanmar, Philippines and Vietnam.\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;Philip Visit and give Brochure 21/5/07&lt;/p&gt;', '48', '5', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, '2013-11-21 17:07:37', '77', '', '2014-01-15', 'http://www.synteccon.com/', '0', '0', '0', 0, '', NULL, '0', '', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL),
