(1086, 'UBE Nylon', 0, NULL, NULL, '*', '02-263-6600', '', '02-685-3022', '87/2  CRC Building All Season Complex 9th Fl ,Lumpini, Pathumwan\nBangkok,10330', NULL, '', '&lt;p&gt;Philip Visit and give Brochure 19/6/07 Fax: TCL Marketing +66 (0) 2685-3024 RFT Marketing +66 (0) 2685-3024 UNT Marketing +66 (0) 2685-3042 TSL Marketing +66 (0) 2685-3056 Ube Nylon (Thailand) Limited (UNT) Established in June 1995 as a joint venture between Ube Industries, TPI Polene and Nissho Iwai, UNT started to produce Nylon-6 resin (monofilament grade, film grade and injection grade) with an initial capacity of 15,000 tons/year. Today, Ube Industries maintains 100% share in the company and the production capacity has been increased to 24,500 tons/year. UNT is the first specialist manufacturer of engineering plastic &quot;Nylon-6 resin&quot; in Thailand from monomer to compound. To improve the company\'s product specialty in engineering plastic, UNT initiated production of Nylon Compounding with a capacity of 6,000 tons/year in 2002. UNT\'s new compound factory will usher in a more advanced technology from overseas, enabling the company to serve a much wider customer base. The demand for Nylon Compounding has dramatically increased during the past few years, especially for intake manifold and automotive module applications and this trend is expected to continue. UNT complies with the latest ISO and other recognized quality standards to become even more competitive. UNT received ISO 9001, ISO 14001 and TIS/OHSAS 18001 certification. In addition to global standard, UNT strictly follows quality practice and process improvement such as Total Productive Manufacturing (TPM), KAIZEN and 5S.&lt;/p&gt;', '47', '1', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, '2012-01-16 10:54:23', NULL, '2', '0000-00-00', '', '', '0', '0', 0, '', NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL),
