(1255, 'AstraZeneca Thailand Ltd', 0, NULL, NULL, 'anchalee.surapraphant@astrazeneca.com', '02 739 747400  Ext 404', '', '02 739 7499', 'Asia Center Building Building 19th Fl. \n173/20 South Sathorn Road Rd., Thungmahamek, Sathorn, \nBangkok 10120 Thailand', '', '', 'The company in Thailand is involved in the marketing of AstraZeneca&rsquo;s research based pharmaceutical products in the anti-infective, cardiovascular, central nervous system, gastrointestinal, oncology and respiratory. Some of its major products are Arimidex, Brilinta, Casodex, CRESTOR, Cubicin, Diprivan, Faslodex, Iressa, Losec, Meronem, Nexium, Nolvadex, Onglyza, Plendil, Pulmicort, Rhinocort, Seroquel, Symbicort, Tebranic and Xylocaine.\r\n\r\nAstraZeneca is a major international healthcare business engaged in the research, development, manufacturing, and marketing of prescription pharmaceuticals and the supply of healthcare services. It is one of the top ten pharmaceutical companies in the world with healthcare sales of over US$30 billion+ and leading positions in sales of central nervous systems (CNS), cardiovascular (CV), gastrointestinal (GI), oncology, and respiratory products.\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;Philip Visit and give Brochure 17/3/07 K.Wanvisa 02 739 7431 K.Anchalee 02 739 7404&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;sent email introduction.Christian&lt;/p&gt;', '21', '4', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, '2013-12-03 10:57:08', '77', '24', '2014-01-15', 'www.astrazeneca.com', '0', '5', '0', 5, '', NULL, '0', '', '', 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 2, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL),
(1256, 'Ayudhya Allianz CPLife Pcl', NULL, 54, NULL, 'kamonvan.p@azay.co.th', '02-305-7000', '', '02-305-7999 Ext. 8127', '2rd Floor, Ploenchit Tower, \r\n898 Ploenchit Road, \r\nBangkok, 10330', '', '', 'Bank of Ayudhya PCL., known in Thailand as &ldquo;Krungsri&rdquo;, along with its subsidiaries is collectively referred to as Krungsri Group. Krungsri (SET symbol: BAY), established on April 1, 1945, and its ordinary shares were listed on the Stock Exchange of Thailand in 1977. The Group engages in businesses permitted under the Financial Institution Business Act, the Securities and Exchange Act, and other related laws, and is under supervision of the Bank of Thailand (BOT) and the Securities and Exchange Commission (the SEC).\r\n\r\nIn January 2007, Krungsri and GE Capital, a global consumer financial services firm, became strategic partners which has proven to very successful for all of our stakeholders. The overall goal was to leverage the synergy of the two partners enabling Krungsri to become a leading universal bank in Thailand with a global perspective, providing a comprehensive range of banking products and services. \r\n\r\nToday, Krungsri Group is the fifth largest bank in Thailand with 837 billion baht in loans, 702 billion baht in deposits and 1.1 trillion in total assets. The Krungsri Group serves over 8 million retail and commercial customers through 601 domestic and 4 overseas branches and over 17,000 touch points nationwide. A leader in consumer finance, the Krungsri Group is today number 1 in personal loans and credit cards and number 2 in auto hire-purchase in the Thai market place. Krungsri has been consistently expanding its retail businesses through both acquisitions and organic growth, with retail loans now representing 50% of the loan portfolio. \r\n\r\nKrungsri brand is centered around simplicity. &ldquo;Krungsri&hellip;Make Life Simple&rdquo; is the commitment to making the right investments in our business to continuously streamline the banking experience for the customer benefits. Krungsri much believes that banking should be easy to understand, connect with the ever-evolving financial needs of our customers and empower them to achieve their goals and dreams. Krungsri has been spearheading innovation in this area by offering integrated and simplified products like special high-yield savings accounts, no-fee ATMs, and quickpay using smartphones/tablets to offer convenient payment solutions.\r\n\r\nKrungsri Group products and services include:\r\n&bull; Deposit services\r\n&bull; Lending services\r\n&bull; International trade and money transfer services\r\n&bull; Bill payment service\r\n&bull; Electronic banking service\r\n&bull; Exclusive banking service\r\n&bull; Foreign exchange and remittance service\r\n&bull; Investment banking service\r\n&bull; Securities business, custody and trustee services\r\n&bull; Treasury and related services\r\n&bull; Auto hire purchase\r\n&bull; Mortgages\r\n&bull; Personal loans\r\n&bull; Credit cards\r\n&bull; Microfinance\r\n&bull; Leasing\r\n&bull; Factoring\r\n&bull; Insurance\r\n&bull; Wealth management\r\n\r\nSo far, 2013 is a truly momentous year for Krungsri Group with its efforts to make life simple for our customers. Achievements of Krungsri Auto, the Srisawad microfinance business, our mobile banking and quick pay solutions, to name just a few, has been realized through numerous local and international awards. Similarly, efforts to make Krungsri an employer of choice were rewarded by winning the widely-respected Gallup organization&rsquo;s Great Workplace Award, one of only 32 companies selected globally and the only one company from Thailand.\r\n\r\n&lt;p&gt;Walaiporn Rukkhachart move to a new department and replace by K. Apichada.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;K. Stephen Appleyard Call and send E-mail 5/2/07 (have transpro take care)&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Visit give Brochure 3/2/07&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;President: Mr.Wilfred Blackburn&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Chief Financial Officer and&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Chief Actuary: Andreas Rosenthal&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Chief Office: Ms.Sally O\'Hara&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Chief Officer-Office of the Persident: Maximo Joaquin K. Valaiporn (Ann)&lt;/p&gt;', '16', '1', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', NULL, '2018-01-31 11:23:56', '128', '24', '2018-02-06', 'http://www.azay.co.th', '0', '10', '0', 10, '', '', '2', '', '', 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, NULL, 252, 0, '', NULL),
