(1661, 'Ophir Asia Services Limited', 68, 40, NULL, 'kanjana.rattanaprapa@ophir-energy.com', '02-032-4150', '', '02-032-4155', 'Q-house Lumpini Building, \r\n24th Floor, Unit 2403\r\n1 South Sathorn Rd, \r\nSathorn, Bangkok 10120', 'level 4, 123 Victoria Street, London, SW1E 6DE, United Kingdom\r\nTel.+44 0 20 7811 2400\r\nFax +44 0 20 7811 2421', '-', 'Ophir Energy is an Africa and Asian focused upstream O&G Company listed on the London Stock Exchange with a market capitalization of c. USD 1.5billion. It has historically focused on Africa where the company proved up over 17 TCF (gross) of gas offshore Tanzania. It sold a 20% interest in this project to Pavilion Energy of Singapore in 2014 and retains a 20% interest. It also has an 80% interest and operates a FLNG project offshore Equatorial Guinea.\r\n\r\nIn 2014 Ophir entered SE Asia when it was awarded a PSC offshore Myanmar. It also agreed to acquire seven exploration PSCs in Indonesia in a transaction that is expected to complete in 2015. In Africa Ophir has recently added further exploration acreage in Gabon and the Seychelles.\r\n\r\nIn March 2015, Salamander Energy Plc was acquired by and became part of a single larger O&G entity, Ophir Energy Plc. In Thailand, we remain our position as petroleum concessionaire of Blocks B8/38 and G4/50 in the Gulf of Thailand.', '40', '4', '2007-03-14 16:18:27', NULL, '2017-12-08 10:53:27', '128', '24', '2013-11-30', 'http://www.ophir-energy.com/', '1', '7', '0', 10, '', NULL, '6', '80000', '250000', 0, 1, 1, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, NULL, NULL),
